<title>SOUTH AFRICA: South Africa's Eskom bids for Zambia power - report.</title>
<headline>South Africa's Eskom bids for Zambia power - report.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>South African state-owned electricity concern Eskom has bid for a 75 percent stake in a Zambian-owned power supply operation and is investigating the construction of a 400 kilovolt power line through Swaziland and Mozambique, Business Day newspaper said.</p>
<p>Executive director Jac Messerschmidt said the company was was looking to build its position in southern Africa via the bid for the power unit of Zambian Consolidated Copper Mines, which is being privatised.</p>
<p>Power could be sent via Swaziland and Mozambique to a planned aluminium smelter which Gencor Ltd is considering constructing near Maputo, he added.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
